      "name": "CFD model credibility claim for absolute hemolysis prediction in VAD COU",
      "description": "The CFD-based hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump achieves sufficient credibility to support regulatory decision-making on absolute hemolysis index values under VAD operating conditions. The claim encompasses all five flow-speed operating points, incorporates Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, and asserts that predicted hemolysis indices remain below the established clinical threshold with 95% confidence. Credibility factors assessed include mesh convergence, turbulence model selection, blood damage constitutive law, and boundary condition fidelity. The model has been subjected to independent code verification and solution verification activities consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 requirements for Model Risk Level 5.",
      "purpose": "Support FDA 510(k) submission credibility argument for Class III VAD hemolysis performance",
      "scope": "Absolute hemolysis index prediction across 5 operating points; MRL 5; Monte Carlo UQ included",
      "claimType": "CredibilityClaim",
